animal.description:
FROM COOPERS COACHES:
We are excited to announce Cooper will be available for this years draft. Cooper is a 5-6 month old American Staffy blend that is currently a free agent looking to get his start with an amazing team willing to take in a Rookie. He has spent the last month in training camp with the Holthus team where he has picked up the basic skills needed to contribute to his next team. He may play hard but don't be fooled this kids a lover including his love for all things comfortable.  
He has requested to go to a team with an indoor arena and would not be successful at a team like Green Bay due to his aversion to cold weather. He has a real love for food and has not missed a meal while working on bulking up for his future linebacker roll.  With that being said he is also a food thief and will finish off others plates if they are not as speedy as him which has lead the team to encourage him to eat alone. 
Although he is very energetic when he is on the field he also has a very strict 9pm bed time. He is mostly trained to used the outdoor facilities but is known for the occasional accident if its too cold out.  Cooper enjoys walking the track and knows how to kennel up outside of practice time. He'll need a little refining but has a rare upside and can be a starter from day one.

animal.description:
Meet Doughboy. Born approximately November 2020, he is super cute and sweet and loves everyone he meets. He is curious, bouncy, and fun but also loves to be cuddled.

There is a lot for a puppy to learn, so he will need to find a home where someone is very available to him in these early days. He loves the companionship of other animals and requires another dog to act as his mentor as he continues to understand his new world's rules.

Currently, his Foster family is teaching him the difference between his toys and others' prized possessions. This cute little boy is not going to be little for long. Now is the best time to jump in and continue mentoring him. It is going to be so fun watching him fill out and fit into those big paws. Please complete an Adoption Application. Doughboy is only available for adoption in WA.

PUPPIES ARE ONLY PLACED IN HOMES WITH YOUTHFUL, PLAYFUL RESIDENT DOGS.

Our requirements for puppy adoption are simple and necessary.

Our puppies are not livestock guardians, they are family pets that live inside the family home.

Puppies must be placed in homes with a youthful, adult resident dog of similar size. This gives the puppy a mentor and a solid foundation for becoming part of the family.

Puppies are only adopted to homes with someone at home at least part of the day. If no one is home for 6-8 hours at a time, please do not apply.

Preference is always given to those with Great Pyrenees experience.

Applicants must have secure, visible fencing and a socialization plan in place.

The fastest way to be considered for a puppy is to fill out an application. Adoption is not first come, first served. GPRS and its fosters work diligently to find the right fit for each and every unique dog and puppy.

Applicant's personal pets must be current on vaccines & heartworm/flea prevention and be altered.

Adoption Fee: $450 (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($225). Adoption applications can be found on our website at

https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org/

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

Meet Bagel. He's the sweetest, most loving carb, we mean dog, you will ever find! He is 5 years young, a Labrador Retriever/Terrier mix and he weighs about 55 lbs. At his young but adult age, he can hold his bladder like a champ and absolutely loves to cuddle with you. He doesn't have a mean bone in his body. He loves all dogs and humans. He would make for an excellent addition to any family and enjoy family hikes or Netflix marathons.

If you are interested in adopting Bagel please submit an inquiry directly with Greater Charlotte SPCA by visiting charlottespca.org/adopt.

***Because our rescue is composed entirely of volunteers and we require a home check for each of our adoptable pets prior to them going to their new homes, local applications will take precedence. We will accept out of town applications, but any family further than 60 miles from Charlotte is responsible for finding a representative of a rescue local to them that is willing to perform the home check. All out of town applicants will also have to be willing to drive to Charlotte to meet/pick up the pet as soon as the application is approved.***

Online Adoption Application

Brindle came down from Georgia after being surrendered by her owner. It seems brindle was too Energetic and would take long runs around town Visiting all the neighborhoods. She would do well with a home that can give her plenty of exercise and work on her house training. She will need a backyard with a 6 foot fence (as she only likes to potty in fenced yard). She is crated at night and does well with that. She enjoys people and being active.

animal.description:
**Keller is currently living in a foster home. If you would like to meet her or have questions, please email foster@greatplainsspca.org.**
Hey there, world. My name is Keller and it's good to meet ya.
I'm a pretty easy going gal who's looking for a family that likes relaxing and taking it easy. If I had to describe myself in one word, it would be Snugglebug, and although meeting new places and people can give me some anxiety at first, if you're able to let me get comfortable and move at my own pace I think you'll find that I'm quite a playful and affectionate gal.
I do prefer the company of adults rather than children since the unpredictability, noise, and hectic behavior of human-pups can stress me out a little. That being said, I am a wonderful dog for an all adult home and you won't regret taking a chance on me.
Let me tell you some things about myself...
I enjoy a game of fetch now and again.I like to chew on bones!I have lived with many dogs before. I am able to co-exist with other dogs well, and even like playing sometimes. I would also be more than happy to be the only dog in my home.I know loads of commands and will happily show them off for a treat or two!I am able to stay out free in the home while you are gone and I promise I won't touch anything that's not mine!I can be a bit sassy and pushy sometimes but a dog-savvy owner will know that mygreatest desire in life is to please you, so all you have to do is tell me what you want from me.Now that you know a little about me, let me tell you about the home I'm looking for.
I'm going to need a home without any children. It's nothing against youngsters, I just feel I'll live my best life among other adults.I do like to bark at unfamiliar noises so I can keep the family safe. An apartment might not be the best place for me because of that. If you tell me to stop barking though, I will.A fenced yard is always nice for a dog but not a necessity for an older, chill girl like me.A home with lots of love, food and attention - but maybe that goes without saying?I hope you ask to meet me soon!
Love,
Keller
Adoption Requirements;
To ensure everyone in Keller's life is safe and comfortable, she is eligible to go to a home with humans 16 years and older.Keller must meet all dogs in her future home.Keller is currently living in a foster home. If you would like to meet her or have questions, please email foster@greatplainsspca.org. ...

animal.description:
Hello! Im Sonny!
First things first, I need to let you know that Im bonded with my pal, Goldie! We are looking for a family to adopt us together.
Second, lets dive in to more about ME! Im a 9-year-old Shepherd/Chinese Shar-Pei mix! What a combo. I can be a little shy when you first meet me, but being with my pal Goldie helps me feel more comfortable. Once you get to know me, youll see that Im bursting with personality and like to talk, talk, talk. Im eager to go for walks and would love a yard to explore in, and Ive definitely got more energy than Goldie, who is more of a couch potato! I hope we can work on expending my energy and training when you take me home, too!
Obviously, I get along well with Goldie, but you should know I am friendly with other dogs too! Even though Im on the more mature side, I initiate play with other dogs by doing play bows.
Goldie and I have been down on our luck since our previous owner passed away. What do you say, take a chance on a wonderful pair like us?!
Love,
Sonny

animal.description:
**I am currently living in a foster home. Please email foster@greatplainsspca.org if you are interested in meeting me or have questions.**
Hi there! My name is Max. I came to Great Plains after being found as a stray in Arkansas. I'm glad to be in a safe and loving place now but also loved doing all kinds of outdoor things that Arkansas offered: hiking, exploring, you name it! I also like to cuddle inside once I'm tuckered out.
I was scared when I got to Great Plains - I experienced a lot of transition in just a few days! Since I was stressed at the shelter I got to go to a foster home and have a nice foster mom help me feel better. I still get scared sometimes but have met quite a few new people and they weren't so scary!
I'd love a home that can be understanding that I can get scared sometimes. In fact, I might make a good guard dog for that very reason!
My foster mom wants you to know:
I now ride pretty well in the carI do not try to jump fencesI like to play with toysI am mostly house broken (but may have the occasional accident if you don't notice I need to go outside)I am getting better at walking on leash without pulling!She has taught me how to "sit" and lay "down" on command, we are still working on "fetch".I am used to getting in my kennel at night on my own.I would benifit from structure and positive reinforcment.Would thrive in a quieter environment where I can build trust and confidence.I am such a smart boy and would love to learn even more things about the world with you. Please ask to meet me soon!
Adoption Requirements:
To ensure Max and the people in his life are safe and comfortable, Max is eligible to go to a home with humans 16 years and older.Max would do best as an only-pet.**I am currently living in a foster home. Please email foster@greatplainsspca.org if you are interested in meeting me or have questions.**

animal.description:
**Click on all my pictures & you will find a video of me playing with kiddos!**
Hey there, friends! Im Twist with gorgeous eyes and markings if I say so myself. PLUS, Im a well behaved girl.
Im a 1-year-old American Bulldog mix! I weigh about 60 pounds and every ounce of me is filled with spunk and adoration for my favorite people. I adore humans big and small.
I was rescued by Great Plains SPCA's outreach team after being abandoned out in a yard for over a month. Phew, am I glad to be an inside dog again! Despite these circumstances, I am a friendly girl (sometimes I take a minute or two to warm up!), am eager to please, love to cuddle and am super affectionate. I am happy to greet you and will even try to get my big old body right in your lap!
I do love play time and will even toss toys around myself! I am still a young girl with lots to learn (already know sit and shake with both paws)so I may get into mischief like trying to chew on things that arent toys. But hey, just teach me the way and Ill learn real fast and basically, I already have told you Im a quick learner! If I get plenty of exercise and mental stimulation, I'll be the best girl! I rarely have accidents inside if I am taken out regularly!
I walk nicely on a leash! Well, unless I see other dogs. Im a bit of a diva in that way, I am reactive when I see other dogs and definitely want the spotlight to be all on me in my forever home.
I gotto live in a foster home for afew weeks and it waswonderful! When foster mom would leave the house, I got to stay gated in a room and I wasa very good girl. Sometimes she would bring small humans over to play with me and we had a blast! Maybe you have some small humans I could play with? I hope they like having their faces licked because that's my second favorite thing after playing! Then at night you and I can cuddle and watch TV while the little ones are sleeping. All rave about my cuddling skills.
Friendly, goofy, lovable, thats me! Hope to meet you soon!
Love,
Twist
Requirements:
 Twist and other animals dont always get along. To ensure a safe, manageable home for all family members, Twistis not safe to be in a home with any other pets.

animal.description:
Great Plains SPCA is looking for a foster home for mister Benny.
Benny has been adopted and returned five times since entering our shelter in 2015. Each time his family has either had personal problems arise or have not been able to successfully handle his isolation distress and resource guarding. In 2020, Benny was in the Pups for Paroles program where he got to live in a prison and get 1-on-1 training and did well there.
Benny is a handsome boy who is very loving and quickly wins over the hearts of everyone around him. However, Bennydoes have several bites on his record, all from guarding food.
Great Plains is looking for a foster family for Benny that can devote time to working on his food aggression with our certified behaviorist. His foster family will need to follow the strict instructions from our behaviorist so bites due to food aggression no longer occur.
Our goal is to help Benny make progress on his food aggression before finding him the perfect furever family. We really want Benny to be successful and know with the proper family and training he will be able to!
Benny's foster home should:
Have no other petsOnly have humans who are 16 years and olderHave someone home most of the time as Benny also has separation anxietyBe capable of following close instructions by our Behavior Team to ensure Benny's successBenny has long been a staff and volunteer favorite and we don't want to give up on him just because past humans have failed him. If you think you could be a good fit to help Benny overcome his food aggression, please email behaviorteam@greatplainsspca.org.
Benny is also eligible for foster-to-adopt.

Hi there, Im Sarah!
Im a lovely and mellow young girl with a heart of gold. I challenge you to meet me and not fall in love! I adore my people and want to be with you wherever you go. Ill be happy to take a nap or binge watch your favorite TV show with you! As long as I have a human who loves me and a comfy spot, Im happy! Dont get me wrong, I love to explore out on walks, too. I walk great on a leash and enjoy taking in the sights and smells.
So youre hooked and want to know more?! Im housetrained, know come and sit and think I would do just find around kiddos. Im pretty gentle and sometimes a little on the shy side, but my confidence is really starting to shine as I spend more time with the humans here. I also love a good treat, so Im sure we could learn more things together as long as treats are involved! As far as other dogs, Ive had a few pups in my past and lived with them, but Im definitely more of a coexister than a player. I wouldnt mind a calm doggie friend.
I have been pretty restless in my kennel at the shelter, sometimes I bark and whine. Like I said, I just want to be near you. People-loving, sweet and gentle. Thats me! I hope to see you real soon.
Love,
Sarah

animal.description:
To apply to adopt, please go to www.adoptgoodkarma.com/adopting/ and fill out the online application.  

Rufus is about 2.5 years old and 39 pounds. He would do best in a home with older kids as he is jumpy. He is heartworm negative, up to date on preventatives, neutered and up to date on vaccines.

He is part of our foster to adopt program. The rescue will cover his getting vetted by our veterinarians during the foster period. If it is a love connection the foster gets first dibs to adopt. Please fill out an application if you are interested in fostering him. Typically the adoption fee is $380 but if you foster and decide to adopt we show our gratitude by providing a $50 discount plus his vetting.

Please do not send inquiries asking if animals are still available, if you see it online, that means it is.  We only post available animals.  In order to adopt one of our puppies or dogs, an application must be filled out prior to Being invited to meet the dog.

Please note that these animals in most cases are abandoned and therefore breeds and sizes are our best estimates based on years of experience.  Many times we do not know the parents, so we are guessing.  If you are looking for a specific breed or size maybe rescue is not for you, it is very possible you will adopt a puppy we say will be medium size and the pup may be smaller than estimated or may be larger than estimated.  We do our best but many times we are wrong so please beware of this before rescuing from us.

Meet Cliff! He is an intelligent 6.5 year old, 65-pound hound mix located in Lowell, MA. He is neutered, up-to-date on his vaccines, and in great health. He has been in foster care for the past 7 months and is looking for a family to give him as much love as he will give to them.

Cliff is an all-around goof ball whose antics will brighten your every day. He bounces around the house, wiggling and wagging, and constantly has a smile on his face. He truly loves life and is interested in everything.

Cliff loves going for walks, hiking through the woods, swimming, and playing around with all his toys at home. If you want to do it, Cliff does too. Though he may be quite active, he is also a huge lounger. He will make himself comfy wherever you let him: on his bed, your bed, or a pile of blankets he makes into a bed!

Cliff has a few specific needs in his new home to ensure his long-term success. He is best suited for a calmer environment as the only pet and no children under 13. He likes his humans to be predictable and trustworthy, with no surprises. Since he loves to be outdoors running around, he would benefit from active adopters and preferably a single-family home with a fenced-in yard.
Cliff has had a rough go of it over the years. He suffers from anxiety which can get the better of him at times. He has nipped on a few occasions, and though no medical attention was required, Cliff needs a patient and experienced owner who understands body language. His foster will explain Cliff’s telltale signs and guide you through the training strategies that work to curb his behavior. 

Are you looking for a wonderful dog, full of personality and life?  If you are willing to open your heart to Cliff, he will return the favor ten-fold. Please adopt here: https://tiny.cc/ARK-Application #ARKforCliff #JustSaveThem

animal.description:
Banshee is a 10-week-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, and spayed/neutered. This puppy is currently in foster care learning home etiquette, kennel training, and housebreaking. We would love for you to meet this puppy and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
Meet Gru!

6 months old (approximate)
25 pounds
Neutered Male
Terrier/Border Collie mix (best guess)

Meet Gru!  A handsome 6-month old boy making the most of his second shot at life.   Poor Gru was found abandoned near a construction site in East TN just before Christmas.  Emaciated and weak, he could barely stand.  He was taken in by the local animal shelter and went to the vet for fluids and treatment.  Gru had the fortune to be taken into foster care by a member of the vet team, then was transferred into our rescue and another loving foster family has been caring for him since.  He has been gaining weight, strength, and confidence over the past month, and it is time for him to finally be placed into his forever home!

Gru is polite and has picked up many basic obedience commands quickly, and will learn new tricks for treats.  He has even learned to shake with one paw and give a high-five with the other!  He also knows down and is working on stay.  Gru loves to play and is especially fond of tug of war with ropes.  He is FANTASTIC with other playful dogs and cats!!  Routinely goes potty outside (although he is still young and learning).  An eager to please, super smart, and handsome boy!  He is an affectionate boy that wants to snuggle with his people and furry siblings all the time.

We have a few things that are “must haves” in Gru’s forever home.  He does not like to be left alone for very long, so we are looking for the perfect family fit! Do you have what he needs? --- 

-He MUST be an inside family dog with supervised outside time or leash walks.  
-He MUST have family members that are either working from home or are retired so he can assist with all office duties and puttering around the house routines.  He wants to be with his people!
-He MUST have a family without small children.  Only those with kids 13+ should inquire please (small kids make him nervous, and he is still getting past having food aggressive tendencies due to being starved). 
-He MUST have a patient family that is willing to take it slow when first meeting him.  And the family must also understand that it may take more than one meeting to get him comfortable.  Strangers still make him nervous and grumbly.  His foster family is working to help him overcome this fear, but it will still take time.
-He MUST have another doggie friend in the home!  Gru thrives with another friendly doggie that will play and show him the ropes in his new home.  

Could you be the family Gru would like to call his own?  Please email Amanda, at pawsofvalor.ar@gmail.com to request an adoption application. 
 
Our adoption fee for local (East TN) residents is $150.  This fee includes:  Spay/neuter, microchip, up-to-date DA(H)PP vaccines, bordatella (kennel cough) vaccine, rabies vaccine (12-weeks and older),  heartworm test (6 months or older), deworming(s), and up to date flea/tick/heartworm prevention.

Vet references, personal references, and home visits may be also be required prior to adoption.  Completion of an adoption application does not guarantee adoption.

animal.description:
I am a dachshund boy and am approximately fifteen years-old. I am super sweet and just want so badly to love on my person! I will follow you around the house looking for affection. I will entrance you with my beautiful blue eyes! How can you resist? I'm extremely submissive and get along fine with all other dogs and cats in the house. I've never shown any aggression; but I startle and scare easily, so a household without young children would be best. I have used a doggy door in the past and did pretty well with that arrangement. However, my current home doesn't have a doggy door, so I am trying to learn to wait until we go outside to do my business. I am a work in progress in that regard. While learning, I do wear a belly band inside and it will go with me to my new home. I do sometimes tinkle if scared or startled, so I will need a new owner that's very patient, doesn't raise their voice at all, and has time to take me outside often until I get the hang of things. I stay in my crate during the day and sleep with foster mom at night. I wear my belly band at night, but have never wet it while sleeping. 
Now something you should know about me is that I have a heart murmur. I have three different medications that I take, but my medication has been paid for up through the end of 2021 by my previous owner. I will also need to be on a canned food diet as I can't chew kibble well anymore. The homestyle chicken or turkey dog food is my favorite and I take my pills enthusiastically when they are inside my favorite treat... chicken meatballs. Yum! 
All in all, I'm a wonderful boy and would sure love to find my forever family. Could that be you?
If you would like to meet me, fill out an application and the Bella staff will arrange it.

animal.description:
Cowboy and Nola are a super loving, bonded pair. Nola is a 13-year-old red female cattle dog, and Cowboy is a 4-year-old blue male cattle dog.
Nola was adopted from our rescue years ago, and then her owner adopted Cowboy from a local shelter after her.
Cowboy and Nola's owner is unfortunately unable to care for them anymore due to medical issues, and wants what is best for both of them.

These two sweethearts are up to date on vaccinations, preventatives, and spayed/neutered and microchipped. They are both house trained. They adore each other and both love affection. They are currently living at Bowzee Wowzee Pet Lodge in Ft. Mill, SC, being loved and care for by the amazing staff there! Nola may be on the older side, but she has lots of pep in her step and acts much younger than 13!

Cowboy and Nola must be adopted together.  If you are interested in adopting Cowboy and Nola, please visit the Adoption Process page on our website – http://carolinasrescue.com/Adoption_Process.html. You can download our Adoption Questionnaire there, then email it to us at adoptions@carolinasrescue.com. That will start the process.

animal.description:
Olive is a very rare breed found in the North called Hangin Tree Cowdog which consists of the  combination of 4 breeds:
•	3/8 Border Collie for their intense herding instinct and intelligence.
•	1/8 Catahoula for the ability to trail and find cattle, also for their toughness and slick hair coat.
•	1/4 Kelpie for endurance and also herding instinct and short hair.
•	1/4 Australian Shepherd

Videos of Olive:
https://youtu.be/GdVDc0LPwpc
https://youtu.be/S1BcTQUSC0E
https://youtu.be/-UTQWvt4QK4

Olive will be happy with a family that can keep her active by going hiking, running, lots of walks, swimming. Olive would do great doing agility. This breed needs a lot of exercise and mental stimulation to keep happy. 
She truly is a happy girl who always has a smile on her face.

Olive has been around horses and respects them. She has lived with other dogs and has done great with them. She likes to chase cats and squirrels. Even though she has been around children age 2 to 11 years old and has done great with them, we prefer to place Olive in an adult only home or with kids age 14 and older. 
Olive can be nervous with lots of commotion going on at a home with lots of people coming and going. She would do best in a home that is on the quieter side and more stable with a predictable routine. 
She may be unsure around strangers and slow introductions are highly recommended.
Olive is not a good first time dog. She would do better with an experienced dog owner who has knowledge of herding breed traits and temperament. Someone who knows how to keep them mentally and physically challenged.

Olive is house-trained. She is spayed, micro-chipped, up to date on vaccines and flea/tick and heartworm prevention.
Olive is beautiful with a nice chocolate brown colored coat and the most stunning green eyes.
Her tail is docked. Olive is 2 years and 4 months old and weighs 40 lbs. 

Please send an email to NeedfulSoulsDogRescue@gmail.com and request an application.

Willow is a lovely 3.5 year old, looking for a loving and active fur-ever home. She was surrendered to ABR by her owner who did not have the time to dedicate to her, and wanted her to have a chance at a life that better suited her needs.

animal.description:
•• Our shelter will be open this Sunday, January 31 from Noon to 2pm. Come see us! **

Mia is a 6 year old black mouth cur mix that weighs 50lbs. She’s a sweet, low energy lady who just wants to get all the love. Mia is friendly with other dogs, however, high energy dogs give her anxiety so she would do best in a home with a docile dog or no other dogs. Her meek nature makes her a great companion for a family in an apartment or house. 

We believe Mia has been potty trained in the past and would respond well to a schedule allowing her to do her business outside. She is great on the leash and does not pull but walks with you. Mia is an amazing dog that would make a wonderful companion to a loving family.

Sadly, Mia tested positive for heartworms.  We need to get her into a home during her treatment. Heartworm treatment is a three months process that requires two vet visits for treatment within the first 90 days and a recheck after a year to ensure all heartworms are gone.  The cost for the heartworm treatment is covered.  We can provide you with more info about her heartworm treatment if you are interested in adopting or fostering her.

Adoption hours at our shelter: Monday - Friday 9am-4pm, BY APPOINTMENT ONLY, and some weekend hours.  To make an appointment or for more information, please call us at 913-321-1445.  If you have a dog, you can also arrange to bring your dog with you to meet our dogs to see if it's a good match.

Our dogs have been spayed or neutered, vaccinated, dewormed, microchipped and tested for heartworms (if 7 months or older).

Visit our Petfinder home page at http://kckac.petfinder.com for more info about adopting our pets.

Zeus is a 5 year old Chinese sharpei mix and he is 57lbs.  He seems to have been abused before coming to us as he is very nervous when being touched. However, Zeus loves affection and will lightly put his paw on your leg to ask for more Zeus is very docile inside and outside and is not interested in toys but would rather walk around and sniff. He has had previous potty training and with a proper schedule will adjust quickly. 

Zeus is a nervous guy, which makes him kennel reactive and may not get along with every dog he meets. He does not show aggression with cats but definitely notices them. Because he is a nervous guy that was most likely previously abused we suggest being cautious around his food, though he has shown no signs of food aggression. In a loving home we believe he will come out of his shell and be a great companion.

Sadly, Zeus tested positive for heartworms.  We need to get him into a home during his treatment. Heartworm treatment is a three months process that requires two vet visits for treatment within the first 90 days and a recheck after a year to ensure all heartworms are gone.  The cost for the heartworm treatment is covered.  We can provide you with more info about his heartworm treatment if you are interested in adopting or fostering him.

animal.description:
Name: Cob (aka Tyler)
Breeds: Black Lab Mix
Age: Young Adult
Gender: Male

Key traits: active, dog friendly, cat friendly, people friendly.

Cob (aka Tyler) is everything you expect from a young Lab mix. He is happy, goofy, energetic, and loves everyone and everything. Looking for a jogging partner? Check! Looking for the next obedience star? Check! Looking for a playmate for your other dog? Check! Looking for a loyal, goof ball who will make you laugh on the daily with his puppy antics? Check! Cob is about 1 year old, 60 lbs fully grown. He is smart as can be and food motivated so training him is a breeze! He is housetrained and cratetrained. He is working on basic obedience and doing well but needs a home who wants to continue training him and teaching him manners. He is excellent with other dogs, fine with the cat, and while he adores people of all ages he is best in a home without real young kids since he can be grabby with food and treats and kind of a bull in a china shop. His happy Lab wagging a mile a minute booty sends the littles one flying!  Cob is the ideal dog for an active home who wants a fun buddy who is up for anything. 

Requirements: Home with yard space. 

Adoption Fee: $450 + tax. This includes neuter/spay, current vaccinations as age appropriate, heartworm/tick testing if appropriate, deworming, microchip, and current preventatives

Interested in adopting?  Fill out a preadopt application here: https://form.jotform.com/203104997748162

You can email fostersheadinghomek9@gmail.com with additional questions.

This dog is located in Minneapolis, MN

animal.description:
Courtesy post:

Hi I'm Lacey! I'm an 8yr old shepherd/husky mix who needs a new home, it wasn't safe for me at my previous home so my wonderful foster who found me as a stray found my family and my mom explained to her that staying there wasn't safe any longer and although I was loved, I needed a new home. Sky, my foster mom agreed to foster and do the rehoming but she needed the help of a rescue to get the word out.
I'm a very sweet girl, super smart and know a lot of commands. My foster says I can learn anything in 2 days. I'm perfect for an ESA dog, I'm protective of the one I love, even though I'm 8 years old, I'm very much active, I love hiking and walks so if you're up for exercising,  let's go! I love playing with my toys, playing catch and if you want to stay in, I love getting cuddled all day. I'm a little timid at first around men til I know you're nice to me and I will warm up quickly. I love people and nice to everyone but I love my food, a bit possessive and don't like to share so other animals can't be around,  especially while eating but I'm cool with my humans around my food. It would be best to not have small kids in the home.  I get attached to my person and need someone who stays at home or works from home cuz I have some separation anxiety.  I'm not destructive when left but will start to bark, probably scared you won't come back. It's something we can work on or heck, take me with you, I love car rides and another reason why I'm a perfect ESA dog. I would love a nice yard to play in, run and feel free. I'm potty trained and just an all around wonderful girl!! Please reach out to meet me, I'm worth it, I'm spayed, vaccinated,  chipped and just missing my forever human, my best friend! 

Contact Sky at (512)  924-2641 or Theskyvanvliet@gmail.com but calls preferred. 
Located in Santa Clarita, willing to travel for right person.

animal.description: Hi there folks I am Sir Hubert! I've been around the sun a few times as they say, so HCH is calling me a hospice foster. This does not mean I don't still have a lot of love to give, it just means I'm a senior with some extra "stuff" to think about. Since my arrival the medical team noted I was pretty achy in all my joints, but they started me on some great meds and I already feel miles better, as in lets go walkin! During my neuter procedure Dr. B did find quite a few worrying masses on my skin on my belly. I LOVE laying belly up in the sun and I guess no one told me that wasn't always the best idea. Dr. B did her very best to remove as much of the worrying skin lesions as possible. Our medical team can definitely tell ya about all my medical concerns when you come visit me. Please don't pass me by because I'm a senior guy! I would like nothing more than to hang out with my new forever human and share my Pitbull smile everyday!!

Adoption Coordinator: Kristen J.
Location: Foster

The adoption fee for this dog/puppy is $475. This fee includes spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

 We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. animal.description:
KODA is a very kind dog -- other dogs in need seem to sense this, he's an "old soul". He's calm and affectionate, great with kind people and other kind dogs. He doesn't seem to have any bad husky traits. He's a medium/low shedder. Very affectionate, loves treats. He seems to get along with any dog he meets. He's fine with sharing toys, treats etc. A very special dog for a very special person.

His adoption fee includes his neutering, vaccines, deworming, microchip. He was born on a reservation we work with July 2014.

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
Kurt is looking for the perfect home. We think he is around 4 or 5 years old. He absolutely craves love and attention and enjoys giving big dogo hugs and kisses. He would do best in a home with a confident experienced adopter who would work with him on his training and provide him with plenty of exercise. He has not been reactive with other dogs and could possibly do well with a submissive female with proper introductions.  We do not recommend a home with cats, small dogs or small children. Kurt is a big love bug and would be so happy to be someone's adventure buddy. He is currently being fostered in Central Texas but would happily go on a road trip to the right forever home. 

Dogos are a wonderful breed but we urge anyone interested to dig in and do a lot of research before deciding if they are a good fit for your home. They require a lot of attention and training with them never ends!  Boundaries must be enforced and they often need reminders as they push past boundaires you set! Dogos are loving, kind and gentle but don't mistake that for weakness because they are equally powerful and intense as well! Everyone in the home must be on board with having a dogo and play a major role in their daily routines and training. Yes it is work, but the rewards are ten-fold! Lazy homes don't work for dogos as they need stimulation, exercise, and lots of attention too during their younger years.  Our goal in rescue is to be as transparent as we can about each and every dog plus make sure new families really understand the needs of a dogo!

animal.description:
Hope is a 3-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description: Hi I'm Ezra. I'm a typical Husky, which means I have high energy, smarts, and a bit of a mischievous personality. I'm hoping to find an active person or family that can give me daily mental and physical exercise through training, games, interactive toys, and outdoor activities. As a Husky, I'm a natural Houdini, so you might not be able to trust me alone in your yard! If you're well versed in the Husky ways, looking for love and excitement in your life, I'm your kind of companion! I really like to talk when alone, sometimes even when I have company. I'm not sure apartment neighbors will appreciate me being a chatty Cathy. I need a home where any children are at least school aged, I may do best where any children are closer to their teens though as I can be a bit rambunctious. I need a home where I am the only male dog, but I may do best as the only dog in the home. I need to meet any children and dogs in the home to make sure it's a perfect match. Ezra will be shown by appointment only. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . What do you get when you stack cuteness, on top of smart, on top of friendly? You get our boy Staxx. This handsome young man is house broken and loves people and other dogs of all sizes. Staxx is content just laying around the house, playing with his toys, and chewing on his bones. But when you're ready to play so is he. Staxx is super smart and mastering basic commands. Adopt Staxx today, for he'll be out of stock soon. 

Staxx is about 4 years old and weighs about 41 pounds (will put on weight). 

If you're interested in meeting Staxx, please visit our website to learn about our adoption process and to fill out an application, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

All of our dogs and cats will be micro-chipped, spayed or neutered, and up-to-date on vaccinations at the time of adoption. For more photos of Staxx, follow us on Facebook Gateway Pet Guardians and Instagram @gatewaypets ... #gpgStaxx. 

To view other adoptable pets from our shelter, please visit, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

Gateway Pet Guardians is proud to offer a variety of mixed breed dogs available for adoption. However, please keep in mind that we rarely know the genetic background of the animals we rescue and, as such, we cannot guarantee the exact breed combinations found within this dog. However, we do not know his/her actual genetic makeup. Just know that this dog is probably a variety of several different breeds that have combined to create one very amazing and unique animal.

animal.description:
Joy is a 9-week-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, and spayed/neutered. This puppy is currently in foster care learning home etiquette, kennel training, and housebreaking. We would love for you to meet this puppy and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

Thank you for choosing adoption! If you would like more information on our organization please visit our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org.

animal.description:
Introducing the sweet Miss Pretzel!

Miss Pretzel is a 12-month-old female American Staffordshire Terrier mix. We believe she may be mixed with a hound breed as she has shorter, cuter legs. She has been spayed, microchipped, current on all of her vaccinations, and has her wellness exam.

She was rescued with another female dog, and they got along very well together. We have not socialized Pretzel with another dog other than Sunny, so we cannot confirm she will definitely be good with other dogs. Pretzel is crate trained, potty trained and she is very well behaved in a home. She absolutely loves children; she's currently in her second foster home with children and has even exceptionally behaved with a special needs child.

Miss Pretzel is a little shy and timid upon first meeting, and she does warm up to ladies much quicker than gents. Her new family will need to be patient with her and give her time to decompress and settle in. If you are interested in meeting Miss Pretzel,

please submit a completed
adoption application found
at www.doggiebonez.com so that we can schedule a meet and greet. She is also on all of our social media pages IG: @Doggie_Bonez_Inc_ and Facebook: Doggie Bonez.

If adoption isn't an option, please consider fostering one of our pups. We are a volunteer-run non-profit dog rescue and always welcome new short or long-term doggie foster families. We much appreciate the help and time of our fosters. You provide all the love, comfort, and safety of a home, and we supply you with everything else you may need, dog food, dog bed, toys, medical attention (if required), etc. If you are interested, please visit www.doggiebonez.com to see all of our available dogs who need a foster family while waiting for their fur-ever home and complete the foster application.

animal.description:
Welcome Oreo to CCPAL Rescue.  He is a beautiful Jack Russel Terrier.  He is about 18 months old and he weighs about 18lbs.  He is a really good representative for this breed.  He is good with other dogs and fine in the wire crate.  He is also in a foster home with a cat.  He is nice on a leash and overall a really good little dog.  He is sturdy enough to be a nice walking partner for someone.  He is independent and will not need constant attention.  He is currently at CCPAL rescue waiting for his forever home.  He could be adopted locally in Texas which is where the rescue is located or we can work with one of the wonderful transporters to deliver him to Washington, Portland, Minnesota, Wisconsin, Vermont or all along the East Coast.  His adoption fee is 250 and transport is 185.  Rhode Island and Massachusetts are not states we adopt to because of the regulations imposed by these states.

Contact Marlene at 210-867-1769 or email to ccpalinquiries@gmail.com if you have questions. Online applications at www.ccpal.info/ See his cute video!!

animal.description:
***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them***

Coco is currently in Houston, TX and can transport to the PNW mid February.

Meet Coco! She's a 10 month old girl who is full of life! Coco was found wandering the streets, like so many other pups down in Houston, TX. Her finder reached out to us for help after trying to find Coco's owner with no one coming forward to claim her. 

Coco is your typical puppy with lots of love & energy. We recommend basic obedience classes to help this sweet girl get to her full potential! Coco walks well on a leash, but could still use a little bit of work, but we know that with some time & patience, this girl will catch on quick to whatever you're trying to teach her! Her finder says that she does amazing in her kennel and has not had any accidents in her house, although after transport sometimes these pups can regress, so time and patience is KEY! Coco has been sweet and playful with all of the dogs she has met so far. Coco has not had any encounters with children yet and due to her energy level we are recommending a home with kids over the age of 8 years. She has not had any encounters with cats yet, so we're not sure how she'll respond to them.

***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. ***

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for the dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Courtney is looking for a place to call home!  We think she may be around 2-3 years old. She is a really sweet girl who loves to snuggle and give sweet dogo kisses. Courtney would do well in a home with a stable male dog of similar size. She seems to need a buddy around to make her feel safe. She would prefer a home with no cats, small dogs or young children. She would love a home that would give her daily exercise and a soft place to land. She craves human attention, although she may take a moment to warm up and feel confident. Courtney is currently being fostered in Central Texas but would be willing to travel to an approved perfect home.   

Dogos are a wonderful breed but we urge anyone interested to dig in and do a lot of research before deciding if they are a good fit for your home. They require a lot of attention and training with them never ends!  Boundaries must be enforced and they often need reminders as they push past boundaires you set! Dogos are loving, kind and gentle but don't mistake that for weakness because they are equally powerful and intense as well! Everyone in the home must be on board with having a dogo and play a major role in their daily routines and training. Yes it is work, but the rewards are ten-fold! Lazy homes don't work for dogos as they need stimulation, exercise, and lots of attention too during their younger years.  Our goal in rescue is to be as transparent as we can about each and every dog plus make sure new families really understand the needs of a dogo!

animal.description:
While we normally write our animal profiles ourselves, sweet Dixie’s foster has provided us with an awesome write up for our little senior girl.

Do you need a corner of the room or backyard fence inspector? Do you need to look at the most low-key, yet expressive little face? Do you need a snuggle-snore muffin? Then Dixie is your girl! This little old lady has been with us a day and a half and she’s snorggled her way into our hearts! So far she likes to roam around the house, cuddle- on her terms, and snuggle in her kennel. She’s not really into being carried but will allow it. Dixie grunts and mumbles and reminds me of the lady who just can’t remember why she walked in the room. Was it for a drink of water? She is great on walks and really likes to go fast, shocking for a 13 year old , and the only time she barked this stay was when she saw another dog. We think she might be deaf (or selective in her hearing). She loves our 12 year old human and when grandma visited, her tail was going a mile a minute. Maybe our Mimi reminded her of her original owner that had to go into assisted living. Oh! And she’s housebroken and doesn’t dilly dally about it. 

Right now she’s curled up next to my legs, snoring a sweet little song. She’s waiting for someone to make her a permanent lovable fixture. So fill out an application for Dixie today!

animal.description:
Meet cute little 6mo old puppy Jello. He is a doxie chi mix who is a total puppy with no training. He is shy at first, then warms up and is a total busy body. He will likely be about 12-20lb full grown. He needs an active family who will commit to training and social skills. He is not yet house or crate trained but is learning and very smart. He is food motivated and very dog friendly. 

Thank you for reading about our awesome dog. All dogs came to us from different situations and we often do not know much about their past, but they are rescue dogs who deserve a second chance and need patience on their journey. All of our dogs our are in foster homes all across the bay area. 

The first step of the process is you must submit an application in order to set up a meet and great or talk with the foster family. Once application is submitted the foster parents will contact you to chat more about the dog and make sure they're a good fit and can answer any further question. The application answers most of all of our questions and can best match you. If you do not get the dog you apply for we can use your same application for 90 days towards another dog in our care and simply forward your app to that foster parent. 
http://form.jotform.com/underdogca/dog-adoption-application

All dogs will be fully vetted (Spay/ Neutered, Micro chipped, DHPP and Rabies Vaccinated) and other possible vet care prior to adoption.

The adoption fee is $400, which is considered a non refundable donation

visit us at underdogca.com or follow us on FB and IG @underdogca
https://www.facebook.com/underdogCA

Hi! My name is ARTHUR. I am a male, white and tan Italian Greyhound and Jack (Parson) Russell Terrier. The shelter staff think I am about 7 years old. I have been at the shelter since Jan 13, 2021.

I LOVE TO: play with other dogs my size
I HAVE: a very happy, friendly personality
I GET ALONG WELL WITH: families with kids over 10
I WOULD RATHER NOT: be left alone outside, I'm too small
I NEED: some basic training and socialization skills
I AM: a happy little dog that would be great with a family and other small dogs.

STARTING THE ADOPTION PROCESS:

Thank you for your interest in adopting an animal. To begin the process you will need to access & submit an adoption application. 

You can access our adoption application at either PetProjectFoundation.org or on the City of San Clemente’s website, under the Animal Services option.  
An adoption application can be submitted to the shelter, via Fax at (949) 366-4765, via email to Animalservices@scdpanimalshelter.org, or dropped off at the shelter in the drop box, located by our front door.  The San Clemente – Dana Point Animal Shelter is located at 221 Avenida Fabricante in San Clemente.

We look forward to receiving your application and will be in contact with you via email.

The shelter is currently closed to walk-in public, due to the COVID-19 virus. 

Staff are on site during our regular business hours (below), to address phone calls,  offer shelter services by appointment only, as well as handle any/all animal control concerns.

Our regular business hours are as follows:  
Monday – Closed
Tuesday – 10-4
Wednesday – 10-4
Thursday – 10-4

The application answers most of all of our questions and can best match you. If you do not get the dog you apply for we can use your same application for 90 days towards another dog in our care and simply forward your app to that foster parent. 
http://form.jotform.com/underdogca/dog-adoption-application

All dogs will be fully vetted (Spay/ Neutered, Micro chipped, DHPP and Rabies Vaccinated) and other possible vet care prior to adoption.

The adoption fee is $400, which is considered a non refundable donation

visit us at underdogca.com or follow us on FB and IG @underdogca
https://www.facebook.com/underdogCA

animal.description:
My name is Lil Belle! I am six years old and mostly American Staffordshire Terrier (I had a DNA test done). I am described as a sweet portly little lady. I currently weigh 70 pounds, but closer to 50 is the healthy range for me. This means I need a diet and exercise in my new home. I love to meet new people and have no problem handing out kisses! I have been around infants and children 8 yrs and older, but don't always know my own strength, so they need to be prepared for my "bull in a china shop" antics. Aside from people, my other favorite things are walks, playing fetch, chew toys, plush toys, blankets, chasing the laser pointer. I am not fond of rain or the hose, but will wade in my kiddie pool. I prefer my people to be home most of the time as I get lonely. I am crate trained, but can also be left free roaming in the home. I used to be a runner in my younger years, so I should be on a tie out or have a fenced yard (which I'm most used to). I have lived with 4 cats and did great with them all. I also lived with a male lab and we were great friends! I do have sensitive skin and sometimes require calming sprays to be spritzed on me. I'm really a loving little lady that would love to find a home!

Please note:
- Our website (www.neenahanimalshelter.org) is updated in real time, so we are accepting applications for all animals that are currently listed.
-Applications can be downloaded from our website. (http://neenahanimalshelter.org/how-to-adopt.html)
- Our shelter no longer has open visiting hours, so a pre-approved application and scheduled appointment is needed prior to meeting any of our animals.

animal.description:
RayRay is the cream of the crop. I've fostered over 200 dogs and he gets top honors: an all around amazing pooch!

He has a sweet and gentle spirit. I don't have children to test him with, but he behaves perfectly around my 80 year old parents and my 10 pound Poodle mix pups.

RayRay enjoys the company of my dogs and seems to like playing second fiddle to my bossy-boss Poodle. He is potty trained and crate trained. He stays in his crate when I go to work and overnight, in his crate in my bedroom. I'm sure he would love to sleep with you, and would be a perfect bed partner. But, I save that privilege for my little dogs since we're always babysitting foster dogs and puppies.

He was recently neutered and tested positive for heartworms. Thankfully, he has no symptoms and it's so easy giving him his meds. I just hide a pill in lumps of canned food, and add to his dry kibble. Easy peasy!

RayRay excels on loose leash walks, is a gorgeous boy so gets a lot of attention when we're out and about. I've noticed he can be a little timid around loud construction noises. He's happy to meet polite dogs along the way, but gets his feelings hurt when dogs charge the fence at him, snarling and causing a big ruckus. He settled quickly into our home routine.

He learned to sit for treats super fast and is treat motivated (and takes them gently). He gets a treat every time we come in the house after potty breaks and will be expecting a treat from you, too, haha. He's building his confidence every day, now that he feels safe and loved and part of a family. 

RayRay is the softest, squishiest boy and is guaranteed to snuggle his way onto your lap and into your heart!

animal.description:
Dottie is a sweet girl that will love you. All she wants is hugs and pets. She likes to take walks and her leash training is pretty good considering how little I have had her. We are working on kennel training. I can't get her to stay in without crying and panicking when I leave. Dottie is new to a lot so she needs baby steps when it comes to new experiences like bath time and getting in the car. I take her out 3 to 4 times a day so it's hard to say whether or not she is house trained. I let her sleep down stairs all night and when I wake up there isn't a stain in sight. She has had no accidents.

Dottie likes kids and people but it is best to introduce her when you are there. Dottie is smart and you will see gradual progress in her with consistent repetitions. She is okay with sit and I work on her leash respect by reinforcing a relaxed pace with a clicker. She will bark when she sees cats. She doesn't really bark in the house. She recently started to nip at me so I will need to work with her on that. She is a very chill girl and a happy pup.

animal.description:
Meet Date. Born approximately November 2020, she is super cute and sweet and loves everyone she meets. She is curious, bouncy, and fun but also loves to be cuddled.

There is a lot for a puppy to learn, so she will need to find a home where someone is very available to her in these early days. She loves the companionship of other animals and requires another dog to act as her mentor as she continues to understand her new world's rules.

Currently, her Foster family is teaching her the difference between her toys and others' prized possessions. This cute little girl is not going to be little for long. Now is the best time to jump in and continue mentoring her. It is going to be so fun watching her fill out and fit into those big paws. Please complete an Adoption Application. Date is only available for adoption in OR.

PUPPIES ARE ONLY PLACED IN HOMES WITH YOUTHFUL, PLAYFUL RESIDENT DOGS.

Our requirements for puppy adoption are simple and necessary.

Our puppies are not livestock guardians, they are family pets that live inside the family home.

Puppies must be placed in homes with a youthful, adult resident dog of similar size. This gives the puppy a mentor and a solid foundation for becoming part of the family.

Puppies are only adopted to homes with someone at home at least part of the day. If no one is home for 6-8 hours at a time, please do not apply.

Preference is always given to those with Great Pyrenees experience.

Applicants must have secure, visible fencing and a socialization plan in place.

The fastest way to be considered for a puppy is to fill out an application. Adoption is not first come, first served. GPRS and its fosters work diligently to find the right fit for each and every unique dog and puppy.

Applicant's personal pets must be current on vaccines & heartworm/flea prevention and be altered.

Adoption Fee: $450 (Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, heartworm test, rabies, distemper, parvo and health certificate for travel). Northwest adopters pay the cost of transport to independent transport service ($225). Adoption applications can be found on our website at

https://www.greatpyreneesrescuesociety.org/

ADOPTION, FOSTERING, AND DONATIONS are just some of the ways you can help a rescued dog. We have worked hard to cultivate a large network of volunteers to save this majestic breed. While monetary donations are always much appreciated, you can also help by donating your time as a GPRS foster or volunteer!

animal.description:
Here is Sugar's story!  She came to us because her daddy died unexpectedly one night just days before Christmas and sadly she was just waiting for him to come home for snuggles. A friend of dad's desparately reached out for help for this dog that she knows was so loved and cared for.  The landlord said they could just euthanize her but no way was that going to happen!  Her kind veterinarian boarded her for a couple weeks while things were sorted out and we decided to bring Sugar into the rescue even though she ended up not being a Dogo, like her daddy thought! Come to find out, her dad rescued her as just a little pup himself!  We've been told he was an Army veteran that served oveseas and had a big heart, especially for animals. He was driving down the road one day and the car in front of him threw something out the window and he stopped because he knew what he saw. Yes, that was Sugar being launched from a moving car but now save with this new human! It truly is heartbreaking that her time with him was cut so short and we wanted to help her in his honor.

Sugar got picked up in Mississippi by one of our fabulous volunteers who took a long road trip and brought her to the good ol' state of Texas! She is doing well and learning all kinds of new things.  She did go through some grieving, confusion, and even a little bit of weight loss but today she is doing so much better!!  She is a cuddly girl that loves to play and get lots of attention by her people.  We know she was around a dog where she lived before and has done well with other dogs where she is. We do not know how she is with cats but that is something we are working on finding out. We don't know how she is with kids either at this time. 

This sweet girl would love to find a home and be the center of attention for sure. Sugar will be 2 years old in May and is a healthy young dog with lots of life ahead of her. She really loved just hanging out with her dad so she seems to gravitate to the man of the house where she is now but also does well with the female humans too!  Please apply if you are interested in giving Sugar a new forever home!

animal.description:
****Please do not message the rescue asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

Dexter and Bella are a bonded pair. They were rescued from Texas, where there are many homeless pets and not enough space in animal shelters. 

Dexter is the male chocolate lab mix and Bella is the female terrier mix with wirey hair. Dexter is approximately 3 years old and Bella is approximately two years old. Dexter is heartworm negative, but Bella is light heartworm positive and has began treatment. Both dogs are very dog and people friendly and housetrained. They are great at lounging with their people. They would make someone wonderful company. 

 To apply to adopt Dexter and Bella, please submit an adoption application at 
snarrnortheast.org 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
This adorable Pit Bull Terrier is the most stunning lady you’ll ever meet!  Just check out those black and white spots – quite the beauty!

Miss Jersey wondered up to a Good Samaritan’s house just outside the San Antonio city limit. With a little food and love, Jersey never left. Since the Good Samaritan already had a full house, she decided to place her in SNIPSA’s adoption program.

Jersey is not only stunning but also incredibly sweet. She’ll greet you with her tail wags and kisses immediately. She is a wiggle monster and has youthful energy. She would do best in a home where she would get plenty of exercise or have another buddy to romp with. Being a Pit Bull Terrier, she is also extremely affectionate and friendly- even toward strangers! She is smart, trainable, and devoted.  She would benefit from an owner willing to train her and teach her basic obedience. Though we haven’t tried her in water yet, Pit Bulls typically have an affection for rivers, lakes, and swimming pools. They will retrieve balls and sticks though not as enthusiastically as a Labrador. Jersey’s short coat is also easy to maintain so she’ll be easy-peasy to groom! To sum all it all up- she’s gorgeous, has a wonderful personality, and is smart – talk about a triple threat queen!

If Jersey sounds like the perfect companion for you, fill out her application today!

animal.description:
MEET YOLA!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in it's possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4393704.

Poor sweet Yola was very thin and had multiple sores on her body when she first arrived to the shelter. She was found as a stray and had either been living like that for a while, or was not treated very well in a previous home. Yola was growling and exhibited other fearful behaviors when she first arrived to the shelter, but once she knew she was safe and wouldn't be harmed, all she wanted was love. She wags her tail when she sees people, she walks well and calm on a leash, and loves to get lots of pets and treats. It appears Yola is dog friendly, but due to her medical on arrival she didn't get to meet a dog until after a couple weeks at the shelter, she wagged her tail and greeted the other dog but the other dog wasn't friendly. Yola is 5 years old and has clearly been through a lot, she may be a little timid at first when meeting new people, but she's just a friendly girl who wants to know she's safe and be loved!
