I'm not a fan of sharing my stuff and because of this, I will not be able to go to a home with exposure to children. I can be jumpy when I get to know you, but training can help with that. I would do best with an experienced owner that can give me the support and structure I need. Are you willing to take me to training classes to show me the ropes? If so, please fill out an inquiry to come meet me.

animal.description:
Buddy is wiggly and smart stick of dynamite! While Buddy has never known a stranger, his extreme excitement for life will be too much for children and this adorable little tornado needs a mature home to succeed. He has crate experience, LOVES the ball, enjoys car rides, and will make a great companion for an ACTIVE family! Buddy enjoys wrestling and playing with other dogs, but his energy and play style may be a little much for senior dogs. If Buddy sounds like the right fit for you and your lifestyle, please fill out a Pet & People profile for more information!

COVID-19 Adoption Health and Safety:

For the time being and to help slow the spread of COVID-19 we are scheduling all adoptions. First step for interested adopters is filling out our online Pet & People profile at www.myhswm.org,

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Wylie and I’m the one you are looking for.  I’m an active, smart and handsome 1 year old black and white lab mix, around 34 lbs.  I love cuddles and belly rubs – that’s right – give me some attention and I will follow you around forever and never leave your side.  Take a look at my super cool markings.  I love people and dogs – big or small - and I’m great on a leash.  I have so much love to give … will you take me home and be my new best friend? 

*All of The Right to Live dogs are fostered locally in San Antonio Texas and will be transported to other states to their new families upon adoption. We believe fostering dogs and not having them decompress in a kenneled environment is more beneficial for the dogs and builds their trust and companionship in a family situation. Adoption fee includes transportation costs, previous/current medical treatment (spay/neuter, etc.) and a health certificate for cross-state travel*

THE AAC IS OPEN BY APPOINTMENT ONLY!
To set up a meet and greet, please fill out a dog adoption application ASAP or if you have already submitted one with us, call/email to put your name in line. We will form a line like usual based on who has an active and approved application in. We will go through our line to set up a private meet and greet for potential adopters to foster.
307-739-1881
adopt@animaladoptioncenter.org

https://form.jotform.com/42994530730154

Sigrid
5 months old, female, Reservation mix, medium size
Meet Sigrid! This overly social juvenile pup is as sweet as pie. She was found as a stray on the Wind River Reservation and no one came to claim her at the Paws For Life Riverton shelter. She is a happy go lucky girl that is still a puppy and will benefit from some training and consistency but will make a great adventure buddy. She has done well with all walks of life so far and can't wait to find her forever home!

Please note, Animal Adoption Center cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

Please know that our intention is to insure long lasting committed homes for the animals at the AAC. If we feel that an animal and a potential owner are not a good fit we reserve the right to refuse adoption.

-For more info on this pet, to fill out an adoption application, and find out who we are and more our adoption process, please go to our website www.animaladoptioncenter.org  
-We require potential adopters to foster a dog for at least one night prior to adopting once they have an approved application submitted.
-We welcome out-of-area adopters, but please be aware we do require prospective adopters to come to our facility and meet the animal in person. You may either foster the dog locally in pet friendly lodging (preferably with any other dogs you own) or if you choose to drive the dog back home you agree to drive the dog back to Jackson if the dog isn't a good fit. Before you make the trip we encourage you to fill out an adoption application and submit it, to be sure you will qualify to adopt. Adoption applications can be filled out on our website. We cannot "hold" any animal. We have a "first qualified adopter can foster first" policy. 
-We will not ship animals. 
-Feel free to send over an inquiry or fill out an application for a dog you are interested in!

Please note, Animal Adoption Center cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

Please know that our intention is to insure long lasting committed homes for the animals at the AAC. If we feel that an animal and a potential owner are not a good fit we reserve the right to refuse adoption.
